data.enText: the removal of things that are not wanted
slum clearance (= the removal of houses that are in very bad condition in an area of a town)
a clearance sale (= in a shop/store, when goods are sold cheaply to get rid of them quickly)
the amount of space or distance that is needed between two objects so that they do not touch each other

data.chText: 车辆在这座桥下通过时没有多少余隙。
data.enText: There is not much clearance for vehicles passing under this bridge.

data.chText: （录用或准许接触机密等以前的）审查许可，审核批准
data.enText: official permission that is given to sb before they can work somewhere, have particular information, or do sth they want to do

data.chText: 我在等待总部的录用审查许可。
data.enText: I'm waiting for clearance from headquarters.

data.chText: 所有潜水艇基地的雇员必须得到安全部门的审查许可方可录用。
data.enText: All employees at the submarine base require security clearance.

data.chText: （人、交通工具出入空港或出入境的）许可，准许
data.enText: official permission for a person or vehicle to enter or leave an airport or a country

data.chText: 飞行员在等待起飞的许可。
data.enText: The pilot was waiting for clearance for take-off.
the process of a cheque being paid by a bank

data.chText: （足球及其他一些体育运动中的）解围
data.enText: a clearance in football ( soccer ) and some other sports is when a player kicks or hits the ball away from the goal of his or her own team

simple_means.memory_skill: clear 清楚的，明白的 + ance 表性质 → 清算；清除

means: (录用或准许接触机密等以前的)审查许可，审核批准

example: the plane was given clearance to land

tr: the distance by which one thing clears another
vertical space available to allow easy passage under something

value.def: Clearance is the removal of old buildings, trees, or other things that are not wanted from an area.

example.tran: 内罗毕拆除贫民窟的行动

example.ex: The UN pledged to help supervise the clearance of mines.
example.tran: 联合国承诺协助监督扫雷工作。
丛林地带的大面积砍伐

value.def: If you get clearance to do or have something, you get official approval or permission to do or have it.

example.ex: Thai Airways said the plane had been given clearance to land...
example.tran: 泰国航空公司说，该飞机已经得到降落许可。

example.ex: He has a security clearance that allows him access to classified information.
example.tran: 他持有安全许可，可以接触机密信息。

value.def: The clearance of a bridge is the distance between the lowest point of the bridge and the road or the water under the bridge.

example.ex: The lowest fixed bridge has 12.8m clearance.
example.tran: 最低的固定桥下方通行高度为12.8米。

value.tran: (路面、河面与上方桥梁之间的)净空，间隙，间距

rootsaffixes.indicate: = clear, bright 清楚的, 明白的
rootsaffixes.title: clear, clar, clair

partsOfSpeech.dec: clar 清楚的，明白的 + ification …化 → 澄清；纯化
clar 清楚的，明白的 + ify 使… → 澄清；阐明
clar 清楚的，明白的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 清澈；清晰
clear 清楚的，明白的 + ance 表性质 → 清算；清除
de 加强 + clar 清楚的，明白的 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 强调清楚 → 宣言
de 加强 + clar 清楚的，明白的 + e → 宣称；断言
